author: seattlepi.com
title: 2 killed in vehicle crash near Yakima
text:
UNION GAP, Wash. (AP) â€” A Pasco couple died when a service truck hit their car on the shoulder of Interstate 82 about five miles southeast of Yakima.
Washington State Patrol troopers say 71-year-old JoAn Shure and 66-year-old Leonard Shure died at the scene of the crash two miles from Union Gap Friday afternoon.
Brent Owens of Yakima was driving the Ford F-550 that stuck the Shure's Cadillac. He was taken to a Yakima hospital for treatment of his injuries.
Authorities are investigating.
